text: Castelfranco di Sopra was a comune in the Province of Arezzo in the Italian region of Tuscany. On 1 January 2014, the former municipalities of Castelfranco di Sopra and Pian di Scò merged to form the new municipality of Castelfranco Piandiscò. Category:Former municipalities of Arezzo
title: Castelfranco di Sopra
